{
  "texts": [
    "Fabiani and Marrone (2021) explored the circulating antiquities market, focusing on Christie's, Bonham's, and Sotheby's sales from 2007 to 2015.",
    "They present an insightful example of how auction catalogue text-even though reporting incomplete data-can be effectively transformed into a bipartite network (Liew et al. 2023; Newman 2003) of 'items' and auction houses, providing a visualisation of the flow of 33,709 antiquities between auction houses and dealers across time and space.",
    "The study offers numerous valuable results, which are too extensive to summarise here.",
    "Remarkably, the analysis emphasises the importance of 20 dealers within the network, with several of them having 'known links with the illicit trade' (Fabiani & Marrone 2021: 24).",
    "These findings, in conjunction with patterns of sales, further reinforce the doubts about sourcing methods employed by these dealers."
  ]
}